            </div>
            <div class="sched-row">
              <div class="sched-time">45 min</div>
              <div class="sched-desc">
                <strong>LC #3 &mdash; Longest Substring</strong><br />Medium. 25
                min limit. After solving: state the amortized O(n) argument out
                loud. Implement the dict variant.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="sched-row">
              <div class="sched-time">1 hr</div>
              <div class="sched-desc">
                <strong>LC #15 &mdash; 3Sum</strong><br />Hard medium. Trace a
                small example first. Expect to debug duplicate handling. Watch
                NeetCode only after 30 min of genuine effort.
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="sched-row">
              <div class="sched-time">30 min</div>
              <div class="sched-desc">
                <strong>Knowledge Check + Log</strong><br />8 questions without
                peeking. Log every fumble &mdash; those are tomorrow morning
                revision targets. Commit all code to GitHub.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="callout tip">
            <div class="callout-title">
              &#9989; Tomorrow &mdash; Day 3: Binary Search
            </div>
            <p>
              Day 3 covers <strong>Binary Search</strong> &mdash; turning O(n)
              into O(log n). You will learn why binary search applies to far
              more than sorted arrays, and tackle Search in Rotated Sorted Array
              &mdash; the problem that eliminates most candidates.
            </p>
